    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>During disassembly, lay all parts on a clean bench in order of removal to facilitate reassembly.</para>
        <para>When removing limit washers, spacers and gears, note their location. Keep internal-splined washers and
            external-splined spacers with the gear from which they were removed. There is only one limit washer and one
            spacer belonging to each gear.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301791">Figure 91</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301791" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301791" filename="../figg13/g1301791.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 91. Remove Reverse Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove reverse gear spline spacer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301791">Figure 91</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301792">Figure 92</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301792" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301792" filename="../figg13/g1301792.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 92. Remove Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft in a vertical position (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301793">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301793" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301793" filename="../figg13/g1301793.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 93. Mainshaft Key</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mainshaft key snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the mainshaft rear, pull the mainshaft key from the mainshaft key way (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301793">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the reverse gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse-1st speed sliding clutch.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st gear and spline spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st gear spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the 1st gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the 3rd gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 3rd gear spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd gear spline spacer.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the 3rd gear limit washer splines with the mainshaft splines and remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the roll pin; replace if necessary.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
